<section xml:id="sec-equations-of-normals" original="PRECALC/modules/m49455/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
  <title>Equations of Normals</title>

  <!-- Content summary: normal has gradient -1/f'(x), plug into y - y1 = m(x-x1) -->

  <objectives>
 Determine the equations of tangents and normal to a curve
  </objectives>

  <!-- Add <insight> here -->

  <!-- BEGIN BORROWED CONTENT -->

<!-- Borrowed from PRECALC fs-id1165135645114: Finding an Equation of a Line Tangent to the Graph of a Function -->
  
  <p>The equation of a tangent line to a curve of the function <m>f(x)</m> at <m>x=a</m> is derived from the point-slope form of a line, <m>y=m(x-x_{1})+y_{1}.</m> The slope of the line is the slope of the curve at <m>x=a</m> and is therefore equal to <m>f^{′}(a),</m> the derivative of <m>f(x)</m> at <m>x=a.</m> The coordinate pair of the point on the line at <m>x=a</m> is <m>(a,f(a)).</m>
    </p>
  
  <p>If we substitute into the point-slope form, we have</p>
  
  <image xml:id="PRECALC-5Ssn2OniIF-v2" original="PRECALC/modules/m49455/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0" source="PRECALC/CNX_Precalc_Figure_12_04_019.jpg" width="80%">
      <description>
               The point-slope formula that demonstrates that m = f(a), x1 = a, and y_1 = f(a).
           </description>
    </image>
  
  <p>The equation of the tangent line is</p>
  
  <p>
      <me>y=f'(a)(x-a)+f(a)</me>
    </p>
  
  <insight xml:id="PRECALC-Kj91QGUxU8-v2" original="PRECALC/modules/m49455/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>The Equation of a Line Tangent to a Curve of the Function</title>
      <p>The equation of a line tangent to the curve of a function <m>f</m> at a point <m>x=a</m> is</p>
      <p>
        <me>y=f'(a)(x-a)+f(a)</me>
      </p>
    </insight>
  
  <insight xml:id="PRECALC-proemu0n8C-v2" original="PRECALC/modules/m49455/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>
        <em>Given a function <m>f,</m> find the equation of a line tangent to the function at <m>x=a.</m>
        </em>
      </title>
      <ol>
        <li>Find the derivative of <m>f(x)</m> at <m>x=a</m> using <m>f^{′}(a)=\lim_{h \to 0}\frac{f(a+h)-f(a)}{h}.</m>
        </li>
        <li>Evaluate the function at <m>x=a.</m> This is <m>f(a).</m>
        </li>
        <li>Substitute <m>(a,f(a))</m> and <m>f^{′}(a)</m> into <m>y=f'(a)(x-a)+f(a).</m>
        </li>
        <li>Write the equation of the tangent line in the form <m>y=mx+b.</m>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </insight>
  
  <example xml:id="PRECALC-yerTenB3ui-v2" original="PRECALC/modules/m49455/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>Finding the Equation of a Line Tangent to a Function at a Point</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Find the equation of a line tangent to the curve <m>f(x)=x^{2}-4x</m> at <m>x=3.</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>Using:</p>
        <p>
          <me>f'(a)=\lim_{h \to 0}\frac{f(a+h)-f(a)}{h}</me>
        </p>
        <p>Substitute <m>f(a+h)=(a+h)^{2}-4(a+h)</m> and <m>f(a)=a^{2}-4a.</m>
        </p>
        <p>
          <md>
            <mrow>f^{′}(a)=\lim_{h \to 0}\frac{(a+h)(a+h)-4(a+h)-(a^{2}-4a)}{h}</mrow>
            <mrow>=\lim_{h \to 0}\frac{a^{2}+2ah+h^{2}-4a-4h-a^{2}+4a}{h} &amp; \text{ Remove parentheses }.</mrow>
            <mrow>=\lim_{h \to 0}\frac{\cancel{a^{2}}+2ah+h^{2}\cancel{-4a}-4h\cancel{-a^{2}}\cancel{+4a}}{h} &amp; \text{ Combine like terms }.</mrow>
            <mrow>=\lim_{h \to 0}\frac{2ah+h^{2}-4h}{h}</mrow>
            <mrow>=\lim_{h \to 0}\frac{\cancel{h}(2a+h-4)}{\cancel{h}} &amp; \text{ Factor out }h.</mrow>
            <mrow>=2a+0-4</mrow>
            <mrow>f^{′}(a)=2a-4 &amp; \text{ Evaluate the limit }.</mrow>
            <mrow>f^{′}(3)=2(3)-4=2</mrow>
          </md>
        </p>
        <p>Equation of tangent line at <m>x=3:</m>
        </p>
        <p>
          <md>
            <mrow>y=f'(a)(x-a)+f(a)</mrow>
            <mrow>y=f'(3)(x-3)+f(3)</mrow>
            <mrow>y=2(x-3)+(-3)</mrow>
            <mrow>y=2x-9</mrow>
          </md>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </example>
  
  <convention>
      <p>This section <xref ref="sec-equations-of-normals" text="title" /> is adapted from "<url href="https://github.com/openstax/osbooks-college-algebra-bundle/tree/e10e6b91143fe884c7c60dc0ad82ef23e1be0aa5/modules/m49455/index.cnxml">Finding an Equation of a Line Tangent to the Graph of a Function</url>" in Open STAX Precalculus 2e, used under <url href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/deed.en">CC-BY-4.0</url>.</p>
    </convention>

  <!-- END BORROWED CONTENT -->
</section>
